name: 3.6.2-Release
body: Maintenance release. Check the [CHANGELOG](https://github.com/bcosca/fatfree-core/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md) for details.

name: 3.6.1-Release
body:
To keep things fast and clean, this patch release comes with a bunch of bug and compatibility fixes regarding PHP7, APCu, memcached and mongodb.

It also includes some new things like a Recaptcha plugin, HTTP2 resource preload push and more.
Please check the [changelog file](https://github.com/bcosca/fatfree-core/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md) for more details.

name: 3.6.0-Release
body:
Your favorite framework got even better. Version 3.6.0 is finally ready.
For some infomation about the new features, updates and changes, check the

### [**RELEASE NOTES**](http://slides.com/ikkez/fat-free-v3-6)

name: 3.5.1-Release
body:
Maintenance release with a handful new and improved things for a rocket start with F3 in 2016. 
See the [changelog](https://github.com/bcosca/fatfree-core/blob/master/CHANGELOG) for more details.

Thanks to all contributors who made this happen.

name: 3.5.0-Release
body:
We are proud to show the world the release of **PHP Fat-Free Framework v3.5.0**

Highlights in this release:
- more intuitive routing precedence order for tokenized routes and wildcards
- new until() and abort() method for real-time communication
- composer support for fatfree-core
- CORS variable for Cross-Origin Resource Sharing support
- View/Template configurable token filters
- Custom handler for suspicious session recognition
- lots of improvements for all DB Mappers
- and many more

See the full list in the [changelog](https://github.com/bcosca/fatfree/blob/master/lib/CHANGELOG).

Thanks to all contributors and the given feedback. You helped us to make F3 faster and more stable than ever.

You are everything this framework is about.
